Nigerians are to experience more dark hours as electricity supply has been cutoff nationwide due to fault in the national grid. It was gathered that electricity consumers connected to the national grid have been thrown into darkness due to the grid system outage that occurred Monday night.
The Abuja Electricity Distribution Company, Corporate Manager, Bode Fedegbe, had said that light will be restored as soon as the system reactivated.
ALSO READ: Electrician charged for phone snatching
The national grid which is the property of the Transmission Company of Nigeria (TCN), has collapsed for the fourth time this year.
TCN is yet to inform Nigerians of the reason for this latest grid collapse and how long the outage will last.


			
